Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportFanoutViolation(25.10)                      reportFanoutViolation(25.10)

Name
       reportFanoutViolation  -  After  timing  analysis, reports all the pins
       that exceed the fanout constraints in the  timing  library  and  timing
       constraints file

Syntax
       reportFanoutViolation

       [-help]

       [-all | -noGlobalNets]

       [-excNetFile f<ileName>]

       [-min]

       [-max]

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       [-selNetFile <f><ileName>]

       [-significant_digits <integer>]

       [-useDrcMargin]

       After timing analysis, reports all the pins that exceed the fanout con-
       straints  in  the  timing library and timing constraints file. Run this
       command after running timing analysis (timeDesign) or timing  optimiza-
       tion (optDesign).

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each reportFanoutViolation parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man reportFanoutViolation

       -all   Reports fanout violations on all nets in the design.

       -excNetFile <fileName>
              Specifies  a  file  that lists the names of hierarchical nets to
              exclude from the report.

       -max   Reports violations of maximum fanout constraints.

       -min   Reports violations of minimum fanout constraints.

              Note: Parameters -min and -max are mutually exclusive.

       -noGlobalNets
              Reports fanout violations on  all  nets  except  for  power  and
              ground nets.

              Note: Parameters -all and -noGlobalNets are mutually exclusive.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies the report file.

       -selNetFile <fileName>
              Specifies  a file that lists the names of hierarchical nets that
              are considered for the report. Only these net names are  consid-
              ered for inclusion in the violation report.

              Note:  The parameters, -selNetFile and -excNetFile are not mutu-
              ally exclusive. If both parameters are specified,  the  -excNet-
              File parameter overides the -selNetFile parameter.

       -significant_digits <integer>
              Allows the user to specify the number of significant digits.

              Default: 3

       -useDrcMargin
              Generates  a report using the margin value that you specify with
              the -opt_drv_margin parameter of the  setOptMode command.

Example
       The following command reports the pins that exceed the  maximum  fanout
       constraints in a file named maxFanout.report:

       reportFanoutViolation -outfile maxFanout.report

